The paper deals with optimization problems involving submodular functions, which are commonly studied in the areas of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The specific applications discussed in the paper, such as ad allocation and information ranking, also suggest these categories.
